desc: Causes the targeted unit to blend in with the forest, becoming invisible to enemies and gaining a movement speed bonus when near a tree.  If the unit moves away from a tree or the spell is cast on a unit with no nearby trees, Nature's Guise is lost.  Treant Protector can cast spells and remain invisible under Nature's Guise.
notes:
If cast on a unit that isn't near a tree, it will lose the invisibility almost instantly.
Nature's Guise checks in 1 second intervals for nearby trees, removing invisibility if none are found.
lore: The Protectors don't often come into vision; their natural state being nestled within their leafy brethren.
name: treant_natures_guise

desc: Treant plants a life-sapping seed in an enemy unit, draining its health, while simultaneously slowing it. The seed heals friendly units around it equal to the amount drained.  Pulses 6 times.
lore: Rooftrellen nurtures the beings under his stewardship, sustained by the lifeforce of trespassers into his sacred ground.
name: treant_leech_seed

desc: Infuses the target hero or structure with a protective coating which grants bonus regeneration. Also blocks some damage from all sources . Dispels when a number of damage instances are taken.
notes: Can be cast through the minimap.
lore: The roots and tendrils of the Treant Protectors are far-reaching, stimulating the growth and rejuvenation of all of nature.
name: treant_living_armor

cmb:
MANA COST: 150/175/200
COOLDOWN: 70
desc:
Summons an overgrowth of vines and branches around Treant that prevent afflicted enemies from moving, blinking, going invisible, or attacking.
Upgradable by Aghanim's Scepter.
notes: Works on magic immune units, but if units gain magic immunity after the effect starts, they'll break free. Scepter grants a new ability, Eyes in the Forest.
lore: Rooftrellen calls the ancestral spirit of nature, releasing its power through all of his kin.
name: treant_overgrowth

desc: Treant Protector enchants a tree, which grants him unobstructed vision in that location. If Overgrowth is cast, units within a 800 radius of a summoned tree will be ensnared and damaged.
